  "subject": "📊 Daily Portfolio: Markets closed | VERA PDUFA Tuesday — binary decision",
  "html_body": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1.0\"><title>Portfolio Check Jul 5</title></head>\n<body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#0a0f1a;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Helvetica Neue',Arial,sans-serif;color:#e2e8f0;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#0a0f1a;\"><tr><td align=\"center\" style=\"padding:16px;\">\n<table width=\"600\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:600px;width:100%;\">\n\n<!-- HEADER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e3a5f,#0f2744);border-radius:12px 12px 0 0;padding:24px 28px;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td><div style=\"font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;color:#60a5fa;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600;\">Daily Portfolio Review</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;margin-top:4px;\">&#128202; Saturday, July 5, 2026</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;margin-top:3px;\">Markets closed &middot; Last close: July 3, 2026 (early close 1 PM ET) &middot; Kuwait 6:00 AM</div></td>\n<td align=\"right\"><div style=\"background:#1e293b;border:1px solid #f59e0b;border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;text-align:center;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">Next event</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:700;color:#f59e0b;\">2 DAYS</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#fbbf24;font-weight:600;\">VERA PDUFA</div></div></td>\n</tr></table></td></tr>\n\n<!-- SUMMARY STRIP -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:18px 28px;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:33%;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:3px;\">Positions</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">$430.62</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#ef4444;\">&minus;$20.77 (&minus;4.6%)</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:34%;border-left:1px solid #1e293b;border-right:1px solid #1e293b;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:3px;\">Cash</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">$352.56</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;\">Dry powder</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:33%;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:3px;\">Total Account</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">$783.18</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;\">Goal: $1,000</div>\n</td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"margin-top:12px;background:#1e293b;border-radius:6px;padding:10px 14px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#f8fafc;\">&#127919; <strong>Withdrawal goal:</strong> $783.18 / $1,000 &mdash; <strong style=\"color:#f59e0b;\">$216.82 to go (78.3%)</strong></div>\n<div style=\"background:#334155;border-radius:3px;height:5px;margin-top:6px;\"><div style=\"background:#f59e0b;width:78.3%;height:5px;border-radius:3px;\"></div></div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- POSITIONS TABLE -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;margin-bottom:10px;\">&#128203; Positions &mdash; Last Known Prices (July 3 close)</div>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"7\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;\">\n<tr style=\"background:#0f172a;font-size:9px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">\n<td style=\"padding:7px 6px;border-radius:5px 0 0 0;\">Status</td><td style=\"padding:7px 6px;\">Ticker</td><td style=\"padding:7px 6px;\">Themes</td>\n<td style=\"padding:7px 6px;text-align:right;\">Last</td><td style=\"padding:7px 6px;text-align:right;\">P&amp;L $</td><td style=\"padding:7px 6px;text-align:right;border-radius:0 5px 0 0;\">P&amp;L %</td></tr>\n<tr style=\"border-top:1px solid #1e293b;\">\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><span style=\"background:#1c1400;color:#f59e0b;font-size:9px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:10px;\">&#9888; WATCH</span></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">VERA</strong><div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;\">6 sh &middot; avg $42.00</div></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#818cf8;font-size:9px;padding:2px 5px;border-radius:8px;\">IgAN</span> <span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#818cf8;font-size:9px;padding:2px 5px;border-radius:8px;\">BAFF/APRIL</span></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#f8fafc;font-weight:600;\">$42.66</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#10b981;font-weight:600;\">+$3.96</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#10b981;font-weight:600;\">+1.6%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"border-top:1px solid #1e293b;\">\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><span style=\"background:#1c1400;color:#f59e0b;font-size:9px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:10px;\">&#9888; WATCH</span></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">ANET</strong><div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#64748b;\">1.27 sh &middot; avg $157.00</div></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;\"><span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#818cf8;font-size:9px;padding:2px 5px;border-radius:8px;\">AI Ethernet</span> <span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#818cf8;font-size:9px;padding:2px 5px;border-radius:8px;\">Data Center</span></td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#f8fafc;font-weight:600;\">$137.53</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#ef4444;font-weight:600;\">&minus;$24.70</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;color:#ef4444;font-weight:600;\">&minus;12.4%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"border-top:2px solid #334155;background:#0f172a;\">\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"padding:9px 6px;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">Total</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">$430.62</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#ef4444;\">&minus;$20.77</td>\n<td style=\"padding:9px 6px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#ef4444;\">&minus;4.6%</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#475569;margin-top:6px;padding-bottom:14px;\">July 3 was an early close (1 PM ET), observed holiday for July 4 Independence Day.</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- VERA PDUFA ALERT -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#1a0a00;border:1px solid #f59e0b;border-left:4px solid #f59e0b;border-radius:8px;padding:18px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:6px;\">&#128680; VERA PDUFA &mdash; TUESDAY JULY 7 (2 DAYS)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#fcd34d;margin-bottom:12px;\">Atacicept BLA &middot; IgA Nephropathy &middot; Accelerated Approval &middot; FDA ruling expected by 5 PM ET Tuesday</div>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\"><tr>\n<td style=\"width:50%;padding-right:5px;vertical-align:top;\">\n<div style=\"background:#052e16;border:1px solid #059669;border-radius:6px;padding:11px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#6ee7b7;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:5px;\">&#10003; APPROVAL</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#a7f3d0;\">TP1: $55 (+28.9%)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#6ee7b7;margin-top:4px;\">Sell 3 sh at $55:<br>Gross +$37.02 &minus; $3 commission<br><strong>Net: +$34.02</strong><br>Hold 3 sh for TP2 $78</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:50%;padding-left:5px;vertical-align:top;\">\n<div style=\"background:#2d0000;border:1px solid #dc2626;border-radius:6px;padding:11px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#fca5a5;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:5px;\">&#9760; CRL</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fca5a5;\">~$10&ndash;15 (&minus;70%)</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#fca5a5;margin-top:4px;\">Position: ~$60&ndash;90 value<br>Loss: &minus;$157 to &minus;$192<br><span style=\"opacity:0.8;\">Stop $24.50 irrelevant &mdash; gaps through</span></div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"background:#1c1400;border:1px solid #78350f;border-radius:6px;padding:12px;margin-bottom:10px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:6px;\">TRIM NOW vs HOLD?</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#fcd34d;line-height:1.7;\">\nSelling 6 shares now: ($42.66&minus;$42.00)&times;6 = <strong>+$3.96 gross</strong><br>\nExit commission &minus;$3.00 &rarr; <strong>Net: +$0.96</strong>. You&rsquo;d give up PDUFA upside for 96 cents.<br><br>\n<strong style=\"color:#fbbf24;\">Recommendation: HOLD all 6 shares through Tuesday.</strong><br>\nThesis intact. ORIGIN 3: &minus;46% proteinuria vs placebo (NEJM). BTD + Priority Review. 89% approval probability. First dual BAFF+APRIL modulator. 14 analysts Strong Buy, avg target $78.\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#fcd34d;line-height:1.7;\"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Mon Jul 6 = last trim window if conviction changes. Tue Jul 7 = FDA ruling. Wed Jul 8 = execute TP1 (approved) or assess damage (CRL).</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- ANET STOP ALERT -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#1a1400;border-left:3px solid #f59e0b;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:7px;\">&#9888; ANET &mdash; STOP $135 &middot; PRICE $137.53 &middot; 1.8% GAP &mdash; WATCH MONDAY OPEN</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#fcd34d;line-height:1.7;\">\nOption B active: Hold to $185 by Jul 25. New stop $135 (below $136.42 real support).<br>\n<strong>Monday protocol:</strong> Below $135 &rarr; exit 1.27 sh. Net: 1.27&times;$135&minus;$3 = <strong>$168.45</strong>. Loss: &minus;$30.94.<br>\nAbove $135 &rarr; hold. AI Ethernet thesis intact (Q2 guide $2.8B, AI fabric $3.5B TAM).\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;\">Stop: $135.00 &nbsp;|&nbsp; TP: $185.00 by Jul 25 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Distance: 1.8% &#9888;</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- WATCHLIST: CAPR -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#1a1400;border-left:4px solid #f59e0b;border-radius:8px;padding:18px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;\">&#8987; Pending Watchlist</div>\n<div style=\"background:#111827;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:7px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:8px;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td><div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">CAPR <span style=\"font-size:11px;font-weight:400;color:#94a3b8;\">Capricor Therapeutics</span></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#64748b;\">Deramiocel (CAP-1002) &middot; DMD Cardiomyopathy &middot; 6/10 conviction</div></td>\n<td align=\"right\"><span style=\"background:#1c1400;color:#f59e0b;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:10px;\">WATCH</span></td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"margin-top:10px;background:#0f172a;border-radius:5px;padding:9px 12px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;\">$22.74</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#ef4444;font-weight:600;\">Entry target $26.00 &mdash; PRICE DROPPED 12.5% BELOW TARGET</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#94a3b8;margin-top:2px;\">Below 90% of entry target ($23.40) &rarr; re-verify thesis before entry</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#64748b;margin-top:3px;\">Stop: $18.00 &nbsp;|&nbsp; TP1: $52.00</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n<span style=\"background:#1c1400;color:#fbbf24;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:10px;\">&#128993; AdCom July 29 &mdash; 24 days &middot; SOON</span>\n<span style=\"background:#0f172a;color:#94a3b8;font-size:10px;padding:4px 9px;border-radius:10px;margin-left:5px;\">PDUFA Aug 22</span>\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:9px;font-size:10px;color:#64748b;\">Phase 3 HOPE-3 positive (PUL v2.0 + LVEF)</div>\n<div style=\"background:#1e293b;border-radius:3px;height:5px;margin-top:3px;margin-bottom:3px;\"><div style=\"background:#f59e0b;width:65%;height:5px;border-radius:3px;\"></div></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#f59e0b;margin-bottom:9px;\">~65% AdCom positive vote probability</div>\n<div style=\"background:#1a0a00;border:1px solid #92400e;border-radius:5px;padding:9px;font-size:10px;color:#fcd34d;\">&#9888; <strong>Bear signal:</strong> June 30 unusual put activity &mdash; 5:1 puts, 2,900-contract Aug 21 $20 put block.</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:7px;font-size:10px;color:#f59e0b;\">&#9888; HALAL: Unverified &mdash; check Musaffa before entry</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#0f2744;border-radius:5px;padding:9px 11px;font-size:11px;color:#93c5fd;\">\n<strong>Action:</strong> Enter only after VERA July 7 result. If approved &rarr; CAPR is primary cash deployment target ($150 position at ~$22&ndash;24). Decision needed by July 14.\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:7px;padding:9px 12px;opacity:0.4;font-size:11px;color:#64748b;\"><strong>VRDN &mdash; ARCHIVED.</strong> FDA approved Lumvoa June 30. Entry missed (IBKR blocker). UBS $50 target.</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- CATALYST PLAYS -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#0f1117;border-left:4px solid #6366f1;border-radius:8px;padding:18px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:4px;\">&#128225; Catalyst Plays &mdash; July 5, 2026</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#4b5563;margin-bottom:14px;\">1 confirmed catalyst (CAPR, already watchlisted). 2 unconfirmed-date names shown for awareness.</div>\n\n<div style=\"background:#1e1b4b;border:1px solid #4f46e5;border-radius:7px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:10px;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td><div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#e0e7ff;\">CAPR</div><div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#a5b4fc;\">Capricor Therapeutics &middot; DMD Cardiomyopathy &middot; AdCom Jul 29</div></td>\n<td align=\"right\"><span style=\"background:#1c1400;color:#f59e0b;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:10px;\">&#128064; WATCH</span></td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#c7d2fe;margin-top:8px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong>Event:</strong> AdCom July 29 (24 days) &middot; PDUFA Aug 22 &middot; MCap $1.23B &middot; Short 9.79%<br>\n<strong>Phase 3 HOPE-3 positive</strong> &middot; ~65% AdCom positive probability<br>\n&#10003; Positive: ~$45&ndash;52 (+100%) &nbsp; &#9760; Negative: ~$12&ndash;15 (&minus;40%)<br>\n<strong>EV on $150 position: +$76</strong> (65% bull &times; +100% minus 35% bear &times; &minus;40%)<br>\n&#9888; Bearish puts June 30: 5:1 ratio, 2,900-contract Aug $20 put block<br>\n&#9888; HALAL: Unverified &middot; Pre-score 2/5 &rarr; WATCH &middot; Say &lsquo;analyze CAPR&rsquo; for full deep dive</div>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"background:#111827;border:1px solid #1e293b;border-radius:7px;padding:11px;margin-bottom:8px;opacity:0.55;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#94a3b8;\">KPTI <span style=\"font-size:10px;font-weight:400;color:#4b5563;\">Karyopharm &middot; Phase 3 endometrial cancer data</span></div></td>\n<td align=\"right\"><span style=\"background:#374151;color:#9ca3af;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:10px;\">SKIP</span></td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#4b5563;margin-top:6px;line-height:1.5;\">MCap ~$200M &middot; Short 26.26% (squeeze-ready) &middot; \"Mid-2026\" data &mdash; no confirmed date (Gate 1 fail). Watch for press release confirming exact date &rarr; upgrades to WATCH. If date announced, 26% short could produce explosive move on positive data.</div>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"background:#111827;border:1px solid #1e293b;border-radius:7px;padding:11px;opacity:0.55;\">\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr>\n<td><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#94a3b8;\">AMLX <span style=\"font-size:10px;font-weight:400;color:#4b5563;\">Amylyx &middot; Phase 3 avexitide (post-bariatric hypoglycemia)</span></div></td>\n<td align=\"right\"><span style=\"background:#374151;color:#9ca3af;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:10px;\">SKIP</span></td>\n</tr></table>\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#4b5563;margin-top:6px;line-height:1.5;\">First-in-class GLP-1 receptor <em>antagonist</em> &middot; 78 patients enrolled March 2026 &middot; \"Q3 2026\" readout &mdash; no confirmed date. $150M peak revenue ceiling limits upside. Watch for topline announcement.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- CASH DEPLOYMENT -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#f8fafc;margin-bottom:10px;\">&#128181; Cash Deployment &mdash; $352.56 Available</div>\n<div style=\"background:#1e293b;border-radius:5px;padding:12px;font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.7;\">\n<strong style=\"color:#f59e0b;\">HOLD. Do not deploy before VERA PDUFA Tuesday July 7.</strong> Deployable: $352.56&minus;$3 reserve = $349.56.<br><br>\n<strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">If VERA approved &rarr;</strong> Trim 3 sh at TP1 $55 (+$34 net). Cash ~$386. Enter CAPR $150 position (6&ndash;7 sh at ~$22&ndash;24 + $3 commission). Remaining cash: ~$230.<br>\n<strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">If VERA CRL &rarr;</strong> Hold $352 as cushion. No new positions. Assess after dust settles (&ge;1 week).<br><strong>Your call.</strong>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#111827;border-left:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-right:1px solid #1e3a5f;padding:0 28px 16px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#1e1b4b;border:1px solid #6366f1;border-radius:8px;padding:18px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:9px;color:#818cf8;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:3px;\">&#128218; Today&rsquo;s Concept &middot; #17</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#e0e7ff;margin-bottom:12px;\">Options-Implied Move</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#c7d2fe;line-height:1.8;\">\nThe options market prices in the expected magnitude of a move before any binary event &mdash; earnings, FDA decisions, PDUFA. Extract it by looking at the at-the-money straddle (ATM call + ATM put, same expiry). Combined cost &divide; stock price = implied &plusmn;% range.<br><br>\nYou&rsquo;re holding VERA into a PDUFA in 2 days. VERA&rsquo;s July 7 expiry straddle was pricing approximately &plusmn;40&ndash;50% implied move &mdash; the options market expects VERA to be 40&ndash;50% higher or lower by Wednesday. That&rsquo;s the uncertainty quantified. At $42.66, implied range: ~$21&ndash;64. CRL reality is often worse than the straddle prices (&minus;65 to &minus;75%) because accelerated approval BLAs have a harder downside tail. Approval reality is often better. Your edge is the thesis quality, not the options market consensus.<br><br>\nThis mechanic matters for every binary event in your portfolio &mdash; VERA now, CAPR AdCom in 24 days, future earnings plays. Before any binary event, check the straddle price.\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top:12px;background:#312e81;border-radius:5px;padding:10px;font-size:11px;color:#a5b4fc;line-height:1.6;\"><strong>Also today:</strong> <em>IV crush</em> &mdash; implied volatility collapses immediately post-event, even when the stock moves in your direction. Long options through a PDUFA: the stock might be up 30%, but the option gains less because uncertainty (IV) evaporated. Your stock position captures the full price move without IV drag. This is why long options into binary events is a hard trade even when you&rsquo;re directionally correct.</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0a0f1a;border:1px solid #1e3a5f;border-top:none;border-radius:0 0 12px 12px;padding:16px 28px;\">\n<div style=\"font-size:10px;color:#334155;line-height:1.8;\">\n<strong style=\"color:#475569;\">Prices:</strong> Web search / Yahoo Finance (IBKR weekend) &middot; Last session: July 3, 2026 early close 1 PM ET<br>\n<strong style=\"color:#475569;\">Data:</strong> portfolio.json last updated 2026-07-04T06:00:00+03:00<br>\n<strong style=\"color:#f59e0b;\">VERA PDUFA: Tuesday July 7, 2026 &middot; Last entry window: Monday July 6 open</strong><br>\n<strong style=\"color:#475569;\">Disclaimer:</strong> Personal research, not financial advice. Verify halal via Musaffa before new positions.\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr></table>\n</body>\n</html>"
